text.tspan: LBNL ATG's Real-Time Ethernet Fabric Infrastructure (building on PSPEPS experience)
Status known by end of each packet:
Length and status bits are written as trusted "badge,"
All clients (except soft-core MAC) have matched,
fixed latency; therefore no collisions possible
DPRAM is (mostly) a 1 MTU (12 μs) shift register
rtefi_blob.v (machine-generated basd on list of clients)
prepended to each packet in DPRAM
